modules.description: Provides functions to parse, apply, and combine CSS-like style rules, including color manipulation, font weight adjustments, and margin calculations. Works with nested records representing style properties and lists of style overrides. Used to dynamically generate themed UI components and apply responsive design rules at runtime.

Provides a way to retrieve and manipulate configuration values with fallback defaults. Works with a record type containing string-based keys and values. Used to access environment variables and command-line arguments with specified default behaviors.

Combines style rule parsing and configuration management into a unified system for dynamic UI generation. Handles nested style records and string-keyed configuration maps, supporting operations like color blending, font weight scaling, and value fallback resolution. Enables responsive design through style overrides and environment-aware configuration retrieval. Examples include adjusting text colors based on theme, applying margin rules conditionally, and loading CLI arguments with default values.

Provides functions to create and update progress bars during iterative processes, with support for tracking iteration count, elapsed time, and estimated completion. Works with integers for progress tracking and strings for display formatting. Used to visualize the progress of long-running loops or batch processing tasks.

Manages dynamic UI styling and configuration through nested records and string maps, enabling operations like color blending, font scaling, and value fallback. Supports environment-aware adjustments and conditional style application. Allows theme-based color changes, margin rule application, and CLI argument loading with defaults. Provides structured access to styles and configurations for responsive, adaptable interfaces.
